8. Quaestor: the text has been corrupted through misunderstanding as to where the previous sentence ended (cf. below, on 18, 4). Thus, Quaestor was thrown back into the preceding sentence in spite of chro- nology (cf. eg. HV). Beginning then with Deinde, the supposed lack of an official title was ignorantly supplied by inserting aedilis (but Cato was not aedile until 199), or praetor (though he was not praetor be· fore 198). Most of the Mss. —to complete the confusion—combine both of these interpolations. Thus, quaestor deinde aedilis· quadriennio post factus sum praetor-quem 1>Ι;·ῑνῐΑ2 marg.
